{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id142da5d6-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s360rr"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"360rr"},"text":"§ 360rr.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Federal-State cooperation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary is authorized (1) to accept from State and local authorities engaged in activities related to health or safety or consumer protection, on a reimbursable basis or otherwise, any assistance in the administration and enforcement of this part which he may request and which they may be able and willing to provide and, if so agreed, may pay in advance or otherwise for the reasonable cost of such assistance, and (2) he may, for the purpose of conducting examinations, investigations, and inspections, commission any officer or employee of any such authority as an officer of the Department.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id142da5d7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch675/s541"},"text":"June 25, 1938, ch. 675, § 541","children":[],"tail":", formerly "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373/tIII/s541"},"text":"act July 1, 1944, ch. 373, title III, § 541","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 360E, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/602/s2/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–602, § 2(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/1186"},"text":"82 Stat. 1186","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 541 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/629/s19/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–629, § 19(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (3), (4), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4529"},"text":"104 Stat. 4529","children":[],"tail":", 4530; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/80/s4/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–80, § 4(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/779"},"text":"107 Stat. 779","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id142da5d8-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id142da5d9-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id142da5da-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s263m"},"text":"section 263m of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to renumbering by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/629"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–629","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id142da5db-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/80"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–80","children":[],"tail":" amended directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/629/s19/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–629, § 19(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", which renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s263m"},"text":"section 263m of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/629/s19/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–629, § 19(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “this part” for “this subpart”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id142da5dc-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id142da5dd-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Noninterference With Other Federal Agencies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Enactment of this section not to be construed to supersede or limit the functions under any other provision of law of any officer or agency of the United States, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/602/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 90–602","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s360hh"},"text":"section 360hh of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
